%N A365502 In the Collatz problem, total stopping times for iteration of the 3x+1 function corresponding to the starting points given by A248037.
%C A365502 The 3x+1 function (A014682), denoted by T(x) in the literature, is defined as T(x) = (3x+1)/2 if x is odd, T(x) = x/2 if x is even.
%C A365502 The total stopping time is the number of iterations of the T(x) map required to reach 1.
%C A365502 Except for a(1), these values are listed in the third column of Table 1 in Kontorovich and Lagarias (2009, 2010).
%C A365502 See A365503 for corresponding number of odd iterates before reaching 1.
%H A365502 Alex V. Kontorovich and Jeffrey C. Lagarias, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/0910.1944">Stochastic Models for the 3x+1 and 5x+1 Problems</a>, arXiv:0910.1944 [math.NT], 2009, pp. 9-11, and in Jeffrey C. Lagarias, ed., <a href="http://www.ams.org/bookstore-getitem/item=mbk-78">The Ultimate Challenge: The 3x+1 Problem</a>, American Mathematical Society, 2010, pp. 138-140.
%H A365502 <a href="/index/3#3x1">Index entries for sequences related to 3x+1 (or Collatz) problem</a>
